codex metadata fixup, as additional read-only context.\nforge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:444:`run_codex_metadata_fix(...)` for **every** status — including `SUCCESS`,\nforge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:451:  partial — codex must be told this is \"natively-collected metadata so\nforge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:480:The current `run_codex_metadata_fix(reachability_repo_path, coordinates)`\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:12:  - `_generate_dynamic_access_report(...)`: runs `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` and loads parsed report data from `dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:52:    Strategy->>Gradle: `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:73:                Strategy->>Gradle: `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:409:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:292:[`run_codex_metadata_fix(repo, library)`](../ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py);\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:316:2. Run `run_codex_metadata_fix` with the merged trace dir as additional\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:103:    Start([run begins]) --> Gen[generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport]\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:149:    ReachedNT --> RegenReport[generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport]\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:192:`tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/natively-collected/` directory.\nforge/docs/dynamic-